{
  "doc_id": "36071",
  "text": "There is also a finding that shows the magnitude of TB burden worldwide. A retrospective study was conducted in Turkey in 2008 on the treatment outcomes of pulmonary TB and factors affecting treatment outcomes. The burden of TB in these finding accounts for defaulted treatment 5.1%, dead subjects 2.4%, failure 0.3%, and transfer-out 0.5% of all patients and among smear positive pulmonary TB there were defaulted treatment 5.4%, dead subjects 2.9%, failure 0.4%, and transfer-out 0.7% cases [CITATION_1] . Similarly in different parts of the world defaulted treatment, death, failure and transferout cases are the real challenges for TB treatment [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
